      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate QoI (normalized hemolysis index) directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "The surrogate output is the normalized hemolysis index (RH), which is the primary QoI for the COU. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is directly evaluable from surrogate predictions without post-processing transformation. QoI relevance is rated adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the COU operating envelope; at least one geometry variant beyond the nominal design is included.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities cover all five COU-defined operating points within the nominal pump geometry family. One predicate-pump geometry sample is included and is cited as evidence of broader applicability. The assessment narrative states the model 'generalizes well beyond its training distribution' based on this single sample; however, no systematic robustness characterization — including noise injection on input features, covariate shift analysis across geometry families, or adversarial perturbation testing — has been performed. The single out-of-distribution data point is treated as sufficient evidence of generalization without statistical support."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence of CFD training simulations confirmed; residual norms below 1e-5 for all field variables.",
      "rationale": "All 4,200 CFD simulations used to generate training data achieved iterative convergence with residual norms below 1×10⁻⁵ for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Solver error is therefore controlled at the data-generation stage. The surrogate itself introduces no numerical solver; inference error is captured under output comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at Model Risk Level 2 for this credibility factor. Scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 guidance for MRL 2 devices with medium model influence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Surrogate model form (gradient-boosted regression) justified relative to the physics of hemolysis prediction; known assumptions documented.",
      "rationale": "XGBoost gradient-boosted regression was selected based on its demonstrated performance on tabular CFD surrogate tasks and its ability to capture non-linear interactions between impeller geometry parameters and hemolysis index. Key model-form assumptions include: Newtonian blood rheology, steady-state flow approximation, and SST k-ω turbulence closure in the training CFD data. These assumptions are consistent with the COU operating range. Model form adequacy is assessed as sufficient for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All surrogate input features are traceable to measurable pump geometry and operating parameters; input ranges documented.",
      "rationale": "The surrogate accepts 11 input features: 7 impeller geometry parameters (blade angle, tip clearance, outlet width, inlet diameter, outlet diameter, blade count, hub diameter) and 4 operating parameters (flow rate, rotational speed, inlet pressure, hematocrit). All features are within the ranges spanned by the CFD training campaign. Input uncertainty from manufacturing tolerances (±0.05 mm) is acknowledged but not propagated through the surrogate; sensitivity of model outputs to input perturbations within tolerance bands has not been quantified."
    },
